#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Running Virtual Machines with qemu-system-ARCH"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:15
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Once you have a virtual disk image ready (for more information on disk "
"images, see <xref linkend=\"cha.qemu.guest_inst.qemu-img\"/> ), it is time "
"to start the related virtual machine. <xref linkend=\"cha.qemu.guest_inst."
"qemu-kvm\"/> introduced simple commands to install and run a &vmguest;. This "
"chapter focuses on a more detailed explanation of <command>qemu-system-ARCH</"
"command> usage, and shows solutions for more specific tasks. For a complete "
"list of <command>qemu-system-ARCH</command> 's options, see its manual page "
"( <command>man 1 qemu</command> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "Basic <command>qemu-system-ARCH</command> Invocation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:29
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>qemu-system-ARCH</command> command uses the following syntax:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"qemu-system-ARCH options<co xml:id=\"co.qemu.running.basic.opts\"/> "
"disk_img<co xml:id=\"co.qemu.running.basic.img\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:37
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>qemu-system-ARCH</command> understands many options. Most of them "
"define parameters of the emulated hardware, while others affect more general "
"emulator behavior. If you do not supply any options, default values are "
"used, and you need to supply the path to a disk image to be run."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:46
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Path to the disk image holding the guest system you want to virtualize. "
"<command>qemu-system-ARCH</command> supports many image formats. Use "
"<command>qemu-img</command> <option>--help</option> to list them. If you do "
"not supply the path to a disk image as a separate argument, you need to use "
"the <option>-drive file=</option> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "General <command>qemu-system-ARCH</command> Options"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section introduces general <command>qemu-system-ARCH</command> options "
"and options related to the basic emulated hardware, such as the virtual "
"machine's processor, memory, model type, or time processing methods."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-name <replaceable>NAME_OF_GUEST</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:70
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the name of the running guest system. The name is displayed in the "
"window caption and used for the VNC server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-boot <replaceable>OPTIONS</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the order in which the defined drives will be booted. Drives are "
"represented by letters, where <literal>a</literal> and <literal>b</literal> "
"stand for the floppy drives 1 and 2, <literal>c</literal> stands for the "
"first hard disk, <literal>d</literal> stands for the first CD-ROM drive, and "
"<literal>n</literal> to <literal>p</literal> stand for Ether-boot network "
"adapters."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, <literal>qemu-system-ARCH [...] -boot order=ndc</literal> first "
"tries to boot from network, then from the first CD-ROM drive, and finally "
"from the first hard disk."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:96
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-pidfile <replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:99
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Stores the &qemu;'s process identification number (PID) in a file. This is "
"useful if you run &qemu; from a script."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-nodefaults</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default &qemu; creates basic virtual devices even if you do not specify "
"them on the command line. This option turns this feature off, and you must "
"specify every single device manually, including graphical and network cards, "
"parallel or serial ports, or virtual consoles. Even &qemu; monitor is not "
"attached by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:119
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-daemonize</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Daemonizes</quote> the &qemu; process after it is started. &qemu; "
"will detach from the standard input and standard output after it is ready to "
"receive connections on any of its devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid "SeaBIOS BIOS Implementation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:133
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SeaBIOS is the default BIOS used. You can boot USB devices, any drive (CD-"
"ROM, Floppy, or a hard disk). It has USB mouse and keyboard support and "
"supports multiple VGA cards. For more information about SeaBIOS, refer to "
"the <link xlink:href=\"http://www.seabios.org/SeaBIOS\">SeaBIOS Website</"
"link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:143
#, no-c-format
msgid "Basic Virtual Hardware"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:146
#, no-c-format
msgid "Machine Type"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can specifies the type of the emulated machine. Run <command>qemu-system-"
"ARCH -M help</command> to view a list of supported machine types."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:153
#, no-c-format
msgid "ISA-PC"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:154
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The machine type <emphasis>isapc: ISA-only-PC</emphasis> is unsupported."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "CPU Model"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:161
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To specify the type of the processor (CPU) model, run <command>qemu-system-"
"ARCH -cpu</command> <replaceable>MODEL</replaceable> . Use <command>qemu-"
"system-ARCH -cpu help</command> to view a list of supported CPU models."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:167
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"CPU flags information can be found at <link xlink:href=\"http://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/CPUID\">CPUID Wikipedia</link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:174
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other Basics Options"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following is a list of most commonly used options while launching "
"<emphasis>qemu</emphasis> from command line. To see all options available "
"refer to <emphasis>qemu-doc</emphasis> man page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:182
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-m <replaceable>MEGABYTES</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:185
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specifies how many megabytes are used for the virtual RAM size."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:191
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-balloon virtio</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:194
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies a paravirtualized device to dynamically change the amount of "
"virtual RAM memory assigned to &vmguest;. The top limit is the amount of "
"memory specified with <literal>-m</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:202
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-smp <replaceable>NUMBER_OF_CPUS</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:205
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies how many CPUs will be emulated. &qemu; supports up to 255 CPUs on "
"the PC platform (up to 64 with KVM acceleration used). This option also "
"takes other CPU-related parameters, such as number of <emphasis>sockets</"
"emphasis> , number of <emphasis>cores</emphasis> per socket, or number of "
"<emphasis>threads</emphasis> per core."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:215
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following is an example of a working <command>qemu-system-ARCH</command> "
"command line: <remark>cwickert 2017-09-01 calling qemu like this will yield "
"a warning: <quote> Image format was not specified for 'sles12sp2.raw' and "
"probing guessed raw. Automatically detecting the format is dangerous for raw "
"images, write operations on block 0 will be restricted. Specify the 'raw' "
"format explicitly to remove the restrictions. </quote> To avoid this, we "
"should specify the image format like this: \"-drive format=raw,file=/images/"
"sles.raw\" This however needs to be done consistently throughout the guide, "
"therefor I'm not changing this for now. </remark>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:231
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.user;qemu-system-x86_64 -name \"SLES 12 SP2\" -M pc-i440fx-2.7 -m "
"512 \\\n"
"-machine accel=kvm -cpu kvm64 -smp 2 -drive /images/sles.raw"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:234
#, no-c-format
msgid "&qemu; Window with SLES 11 SP3 as &vmguest;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:246
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-no-acpi</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:249
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disables <xref linkend=\"gloss.vt.acpi\"/> support."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:255
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-S</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:258
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&qemu; starts with CPU stopped. To start CPU, enter <literal>c</literal> in "
"&qemu; monitor. For more information, see <xref linkend=\"cha.qemu.monitor\"/"
"> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:270
#, no-c-format
msgid "Storing and Reading Configuration of Virtual Devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:273
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-readconfig <replaceable>CFG_FILE</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:276
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Instead of entering the devices configuration options on the command line "
"each time you want to run &vmguest;, <command>qemu-system-ARCH</command> can "
"read it from a file that was either previously saved with <literal>-"
"writeconfig</literal> or edited manually."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:286
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-writeconfig <replaceable>CFG_FILE</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:289
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Dumps the current virtual machine's devices configuration to a text file. It "
"can be consequently re-used with the <literal>-readconfig</literal> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.user;qemu-system-x86_64 -name \"SLES 12 SP2\" -machine accel=kvm -M "
"pc-i440fx-2.7 -m 512 -cpu kvm64 \\\n"
"-smp 2 /images/sles.raw -writeconfig /images/sles.cfg\n"
"(exited)\n"
"&prompt.user;cat /images/sles.cfg\n"
"# qemu config file\n"
"\n"
"[drive]\n"
"  index = \"0\"\n"
"  media = \"disk\"\n"
"  file = \"/images/sles_base.raw\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:304
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This way you can effectively manage the configuration of your virtual "
"machines' devices in a well-arranged way."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:314
#, no-c-format
msgid "Guest Real-Time Clock"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:317
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>-rtc <replaceable>OPTIONS</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:320
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the way the RTC is handled inside a &vmguest;. By default, the "
"clock of the guest is derived from that of the host system. Therefore, it is "
"recommended that the host system clock is synchronized with an accurate "
"external clock (for example, via NTP service)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:326
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you need to isolate the &vmguest; clock from the host one, specify "
"<literal>clock=vm</literal> instead of the default <literal>clock=host</"
"literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:331
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also specify the initial time of the &vmguest;'s clock with the "
"<literal>base</literal> option:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:335
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.user;qemu-system-x86_64 [...] -rtc clock=vm,base=2010-12-03T01:02:00"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:336
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Instead of a time stamp, you can specify <literal>utc</literal> or "
"<literal>localtime</literal> . The former instructs &vmguest; to start at "
"the current UTC value (Coordinated Universal Time, see <link xlink:href="
"\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTC\"/> ), while the latter applies the local "
"time setting."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:349
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using Devices in &qemu;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:351
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&qemu; virtual machines emulate all devices needed to run a &vmguest;. "
"&qemu; supports, for example, several types of network cards, block devices "
"(hard and removable drives), <phrase condition=\"kvm4x86\">USB devices, </"
"phrase> character devices (serial and parallel ports) <phrase condition="
"\"kvm4x86\">, or multimedia devices (graphic and sound cards)</phrase> . "
"This section introduces options to configure various types of supported "
"devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:362
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your device, such as <literal>-drive</literal> , needs a special driver "
"and driver properties to be set, specify them with the <literal>-device</"
"literal> option, and identify with <literal>drive=</literal> suboption. For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;qemu-system-x86_64 [...] -drive if=none,id=drive0,format=raw "
"\\\n"
"-device virtio-blk-pci,drive=drive0,scsi=off ..."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:370
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To get help on available drivers and their properties, use <option>-device ?"
"</option> and <option>-device <replaceable>DRIVER</replaceable>,?</option> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:378
#, no-c-format
msgid "Block Devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:379
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Block devices are vital for virtual machines. In general, these are fixed or "
"removable storage media usually called <emphasis>drives</emphasis> . One of "
"the connected hard disks typically holds the guest operating system to be "
"virtualized."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:385
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<xref linkend=\"gloss.vt.vm\"/> drives are defined with <literal>-drive</"
"literal> . This option has many sub-options, some of which are described in "
"this section. For the complete list, see the manual page ( <command>man 1 "
"qemu</command> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:392
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sub-options for the <literal>-drive</literal> Option"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:394
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>file=image_fname</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:397
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the path to the disk image that will be used with this drive. If "
"not specified, an empty (removable) drive is assumed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:404
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>if=drive_interface</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:407
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the type of interface to which the drive is connected. Currently "
"only <literal>floppy</literal> , <literal>scsi</literal> , <literal>ide</"
"literal> , or <literal>virtio</literal> are supported by &suse;. "
"<literal>virtio</literal> defines a paravirtualized disk driver. Default is "
"<literal>ide</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:417
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>index=index_of_connector</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:420
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the index number of a connector on the disk interface (see the "
"<literal>if</literal> option) where the drive is connected. If not "
"specified, the index is automatically incremented."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:428
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>media=type</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:431
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the type of media. Can be <literal>disk</literal> for hard disks, "
"or <literal>cdrom</literal> for removable CD-ROM drives."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:438
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>format=img_fmt</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:441
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the format of the connected disk image. If not specified, the "
"format is autodetected. Currently, &suse; supports <literal>qcow2</"
"literal> , <literal>qed</literal> and <literal>raw</literal> formats."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:450
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>cache=method</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:453
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the caching method for the drive. Possible values are "
"<literal>unsafe</literal> , <literal>writethrough</literal> , "
"<literal>writeback</literal> , <literal>directsync</literal> , or "
"<literal>none</literal> . To improve performance when using the "
"<literal>qcow2</literal> image format, select <literal>writeback</literal> . "
"<literal>none</literal> disables the host page cache and, therefore, is the "
"safest option. Default for image files is <literal>writeback</literal> . For "
"more information, see <xref linkend=\"cha.cachemodes\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:469
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To simplify defining block devices, &qemu; understands several shortcuts "
"which you may find handy when entering the <literal>qemu-system-ARCH</"
"literal> command line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:474
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can use"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:477
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;qemu-system-x86_64 -cdrom /images/cdrom.iso"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:481
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;qemu-system-x86_64 -drive file=/images/cdrom.iso,index=2,"
"media=cdrom"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:482
#, no-c-format
msgid "and"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:485
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;qemu-system-x86_64 -hda /images/imagei1.raw -hdb /images/image2."
"raw -hdc \\\n"
"/images/image3.raw -hdd /images/image4.raw"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:487
#, no-c-format
msgid "instead of"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:490
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;qemu-system-x86_64 -drive file=/images/image1.raw,index=0,"
"media=disk \\\n"
"-drive file=/images/image2.raw,index=1,media=disk \\\n"
"-drive file=/images/image3.raw,index=2,media=disk \\\n"
"-drive file=/images/image4.raw,index=3,media=disk"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:496
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using Host Drives Instead of Images"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:497
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As an alternative to using disk images (see <xref linkend=\"cha.qemu."
"guest_inst.qemu-img\"/> ) you can also use existing &vmhost; disks, connect "
"them as drives, and access them from &vmguest;. Use the host disk device "
"directly instead of disk image file names."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:503
#, no-c-format
msgid "To access the host CD-ROM drive, use"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:506
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;qemu-system-x86_64 [...] -drive file=/dev/cdrom,media=cdrom"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_running_vms_qemukvm.xml:507
#, no-c-format
msgid "To access the host hard disk, use"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
